registerActionHandler

public static void registerActionHandler(org.eclipse.ui.part.ViewPart part,
                                         org.eclipse.jface.action.IAction action)
Creates an ActionHandler for the given IAction and registers it to the Site's HandlerService, i. e. binds the action to the command so that key bindings get activated. You need to set the action's actionDefinitionId to the command id.

Parameters:
action - the action to activate. The action's actionDefinitionId must have been set to the command's id (using setActionDefinitionId())
part - the view this action should be registered for
